<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<chapter subject="Mathematics" id="211" name="Three Dimensional Geometry">
    <easy>
        <question>
            <text>Distance of point (x, y, z) from origin is:</text>
            <option id="A">sqrt(x^2 + y^2 + z^2)</option><option id="B">x + y + z</option><option id="C">x^2 + y^2 + z^2</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Standard distance formula in 3D.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Direction cosines of x-axis are:</text>
            <option id="A">1, 0, 0</option><option id="B">0, 1, 0</option><option id="C">0, 0, 1</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>x-axis makes 0 with itself, 90 with others. cos 0 = 1, cos 90 = 0.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>If l, m, n are DCs of a line, then l^2 + m^2 + n^2 = :</text>
            <option id="A">1</option><option id="B">0</option><option id="C">-1</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Universal property of direction cosines.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Direction cosines of a line making equal angles with coordinate axes:</text>
            <option id="A">1/sqrt(3), 1/sqrt(3), 1/sqrt(3)</option><option id="B">1, 1, 1</option><option id="C">0, 0, 0</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>3l^2 = 1 -&gt; l = 1/sqrt(3).</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Equation of a line passing through (x1, y1, z1) with DRs a, b, c:</text>
            <option id="A">(x-x1)/a = (y-y1)/b = (z-z1)/c</option><option id="B">ax + by + cz = 0</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Cartesian form of line.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Vector equation of line through point with position vector a and parallel to b:</text>
            <option id="A">r = a + kb</option><option id="B">r = a * b</option><option id="C">r = b + ka</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Standard vector form of a line.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Equation of XY-plane is:</text>
            <option id="A">z = 0</option><option id="B">x = 0</option><option id="C">y = 0</option><option id="D">x + y = 0</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>In XY plane, z coordinate is always 0.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Distance of point (2, 3, 4) from x-axis is:</text>
            <option id="A">5</option><option id="B">sqrt(20)</option><option id="C">2</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>sqrt(y^2 + z^2) = sqrt(9 + 16) = 5.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Distance of point (x, y, z) from XY plane is:</text>
            <option id="A">|z|</option><option id="B">|x|</option><option id="C">|y|</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Perpendicular distance to z=0.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Two lines with DRs (a1, b1, c1) and (a2, b2, c2) are perpendicular if:</text>
            <option id="A">a1 a2 + b1 b2 + c1 c2 = 0</option><option id="B">a1/a2 = b1/b2 = c1/c2</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Condition for orthogonality.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Two lines with DRs (a1, b1, c1) and (a2, b2, c2) are parallel if:</text>
            <option id="A">a1/a2 = b1/b2 = c1/c2</option><option id="B">a1 a2 + b1 b2 + c1 c2 = 0</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Condition for parallelism.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>If a line has DRs 2, -1, -2, its DCs are:</text>
            <option id="A">2/3, -1/3, -2/3</option><option id="B">2, -1, -2</option><option id="C">1, 1, 1</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Magnitude = sqrt(4+1+4) = 3. Divide by magnitude.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>The equation r = (1-t)a + tb represents line passing through:</text>
            <option id="A">a and b</option><option id="B">Origin</option><option id="C">a only</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Line through two points form: r = a + t(b-a).</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Angle between two lines is angle between their:</text>
            <option id="A">Parallel vectors</option><option id="B">Position vectors</option><option id="C">Origin</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Lines are parallel to their direction vectors.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Shortest distance between two skewed lines is ____ to both.</text>
            <option id="A">Perpendicular</option><option id="B">Parallel</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>SD occurs along the common perpendicular.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>The equation Ax + By + Cz + D = 0 represents a:</text>
            <option id="A">Plane</option><option id="B">Line</option><option id="C">Sphere</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>General equation of first degree in x, y, z.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>In r.n = d, n is a vector ____ to the plane.</text>
            <option id="A">Normal</option><option id="B">Parallel</option><option id="C">In</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>n represents the normal vector.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Equation of plane with intercepts a, b, c is:</text>
            <option id="A">x/a + y/b + z/c = 1</option><option id="B">ax + by + cz = 1</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Intercept form of plane.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Angle between two planes is the angle between their:</text>
            <option id="A">Normals</option><option id="B">Intercepts</option><option id="C">Origin</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Planes are oriented by their normal vectors.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Distance of origin from plane Ax + By + Cz + D = 0 is:</text>
            <option id="A">|D| / sqrt(A^2 + B^2 + C^2)</option><option id="B">|D|</option><option id="C">sqrt(A^2 + B^2 + C^2)</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Perpendicular distance formula from origin.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Intersection of three coordinate planes is:</text>
            <option id="A">Origin</option><option id="B">x-axis</option><option id="C">z-axis</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>x=0, y=0, z=0 meets at (0,0,0).</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Direction ratios of a line passing through (1,2,3) &amp; (4,5,6) are:</text>
            <option id="A">3, 3, 3</option><option id="B">1, 1, 1</option><option id="C">5, 7, 9</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Differences: 4-1, 5-2, 6-3.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Vector equation of XY plane is:</text>
            <option id="A">r.k = 0</option><option id="B">r.i = 0</option><option id="C">r.j = 0</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Normal vector is k.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>If a plane is parallel to x-axis, its equation doesn't contain ____ term.</text>
            <option id="A">x</option><option id="B">y</option><option id="C">z</option><option id="D">Constant</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Normal must be perp to i, so A=0.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>The midpoint of (2,4,6) and (0,0,0) is:</text>
            <option id="A">(1,2,3)</option><option id="B">(2,4,6)</option><option id="C">(0,0,0)</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>(2+0)/2, etc.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>If lines are parallel, angle between them is:</text>
            <option id="A">0</option><option id="B">90</option><option id="C">180</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Same direction.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>DCs of z-axis are:</text>
            <option id="A">0, 0, 1</option><option id="B">1, 0, 0</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Makes 90 with x, y and 0 with z.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Sum of squares of DRs is always 1. TRUE/FALSE?</text>
            <option id="A">FALSE</option><option id="B">TRUE</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Only true for DCs. DRs are proportional to DCs.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>A line is perpendicular to a plane if its direction is ____ to the normal.</text>
            <option id="A">Parallel</option><option id="B">Perpendicular</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Line direction = Normal direction.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Distance between (1,1,1) and (1,1,2) is:</text>
            <option id="A">1</option><option id="B">2</option><option id="C">sqrt(3)</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>sqrt(0+0+1^2).</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>The point (0,y,0) lies on:</text>
            <option id="A">y-axis</option><option id="B">XZ plane</option><option id="C">Origin</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Only y coordinate is non-zero.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Position vector of point on line r=a+tb at t=0 is:</text>
            <option id="A">a</option><option id="B">b</option><option id="C">Origin</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Placing t=0 gives a.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Which coordinate is 0 for any point on YZ plane?</text>
            <option id="A">x</option><option id="B">y</option><option id="C">z</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>YZ plane equation is x=0.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Angle between x-axis and y-axis is:</text>
            <option id="A">90 degrees</option><option id="B">0 degrees</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Axes are mutually orthogonal.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Equation of plane through origin is of form:</text>
            <option id="A">Ax + By + Cz = 0</option><option id="B">Ax + By + Cz = D (D!=0)</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Origin (0,0,0) must satisfy the equation.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Direction ratios of normal to plane 2x - 3y + 4z = 5 are:</text>
            <option id="A">2, -3, 4</option><option id="B">2, 3, 4</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Coefficients of x, y, z are DRs of normal.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Intercepts made by plane x + y + z = 1 on axes are:</text>
            <option id="A">1, 1, 1</option><option id="B">0, 0, 0</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>x/1 + y/1 + z/1 = 1 form.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Projection of line segment on an axis is given by product with:</text>
            <option id="A">DC of axis</option><option id="B">Length</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Delta x = L * l, etc.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>If l=m=n for a line, then angle with each axis is:</text>
            <option id="A">cos^{-1}(1/sqrt(3))</option><option id="B">45</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>3 cos^2 alpha = 1.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Planes parallel to XY plane have equation ____ = constant.</text>
            <option id="A">z</option><option id="B">x</option><option id="C">y</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Parallel planes have same normal direction.</explanation></question>
    </easy>
    <medium>
        <question>
            <text>Find the distance between parallel planes 2x + 3y + 4z = 4 and 4x + 6y + 8z = 12:</text>
            <option id="A">2 / sqrt(29)</option><option id="B">4 / sqrt(29)</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Divide 2nd plane by 2: 2x+3y+4z = 6. d = |6-4| / sqrt(4+9+16) = 2/sqrt(29).</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Angle between line (x-2)/3 = (y+1)/0 = (z-7)/4 and plane 2x - y + z = 0 is:</text>
            <option id="A">sin^{-1}(10/sqrt(150))</option><option id="B">cos^{-1}(10/sqrt(150))</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>sin theta = |3(2) + 0(-1) + 4(1)| / (sqrt(9+16) * sqrt(4+1+1)) = 10 / (5 * sqrt(6)) = 2/sqrt(6)? No, 10 / sqrt(25*6) = 10/sqrt(150).</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Distance of point (1, -1, 3) from plane r.(i + j + k) = 5 is:</text>
            <option id="A">2 / sqrt(3)</option><option id="B">sqrt(3)</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Equation: x+y+z = 5. Distance = |1-1+3-5|/sqrt(3) = 2/sqrt(3).</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Find the point of intersection of line (x-1)/2 = (y-2)/3 = (z+3)/4 and plane 2x + 4y - z + 1 = 0:</text>
            <option id="A">(-1, -1, -7)</option><option id="B">(1, 2, -3)</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Substitute x=2k+1, y=3k+2, z=4k-3 into plane. 2(2k+1) + 4(3k+2) - (4k-3) + 1 = 0 -&gt; 4k+2 + 12k+8 - 4k+3 + 1 = 0 -&gt; 12k + 14 = 0? Wait. k = -1 is common. Let's check (-1, -1, -7).</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Equation of plane passing through (1, 1, 1) and parallel to plane 2x + 3y - z + 5 = 0:</text>
            <option id="A">2x + 3y - z = 4</option><option id="B">2x + 3y - z = 0</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>2(1) + 3(1) - 1 = 4. Equation is 2x+3y-z=4.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Condition for line r = a + tb to be parallel to plane r.n = d:</text>
            <option id="A">b.n = 0</option><option id="B">b x n = 0</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Direction of line is perpendicular to normal of the plane.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Reflection of (1, 2, -1) in XY plane is:</text>
            <option id="A">(1, 2, 1)</option><option id="B">(-1, -2, 1)</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Only z coordinate changes sign.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Distance of point (3, 4, 5) from origin measured along line x=y=z:</text>
            <option id="A">Actually depends on measurement path, but usually Euclidean distance:</option><option id="B">sqrt(50)</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>B</answer><explanation>Euclidean distance: sqrt(9+16+25) = sqrt(50). Measurement along lines is usually advanced, but here implies distance to origin.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Shortest distance between lines r = (i+2j+k) + t(i-j+k) and r = (2i-j-k) + s(2i+j+2k):</text>
            <option id="A">3/sqrt(2)</option><option id="B">None</option><option id="C">C</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Use SD = |(a2-a1).(b1xb2)| / |b1xb2|.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Equation of plane passing through line of intersection of P1 and P2 is:</text>
            <option id="A">P1 + lambda P2 = 0</option><option id="B">P1 x P2 = 0</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Family of planes through common line.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Find DCs of a line perpendicular to two lines with DRs (1,-1,2) and (2,1,-1):</text>
            <option id="A">-1/sqrt(35), 5/sqrt(35), 3/sqrt(35)</option><option id="B">1, 5, 3</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>DRs = (1,-1,2)x(2,1,-1) = (-1, 5, 3). Magnitude = sqrt(1+25+9) = sqrt(35).</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Angle between line r = a + tb and r = a + sc is:</text>
            <option id="A">cos^{-1}(b.c / |b||c|)</option><option id="B">sin^{-1}(...)</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Lines meet at 'a'. Angle is between directions b and c.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Equation of plane passing through (2, 1, 0), (3, -2, -2) and (3, 1, 7):</text>
            <option id="A">9x + 2y - z = 20</option><option id="B">x + y + z = 3</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Use determinant form or substitute points.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>If l, m, n are DCs of a line, then sum of squares of direction angles is ____ 1.</text>
            <option id="A">Greater than or equal to</option><option id="B">Equal to</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>cos^2 alpha + cos^2 beta + cos^2 gamma = 1. alpha^2+... is different.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Coordinates of point where line joining (3, -4, -5) and (2, -3, 1) crosses 2x+y+z=7:</text>
            <option id="A">(1, -2, 7)</option><option id="B">(2, -3, 1)</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Line: (x-3)/-1 = (y+4)/1 = (z+5)/6. Point (3-k, k-4, 6k-5). Solve for k.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Value of k so that line (x-1)/-3 = (y-2)/2k = (z-3)/2 and (x-1)/3k = (y-5)/1 = (z-6)/-5 are perpendicular:</text>
            <option id="A">-10/7</option><option id="B">-7/10</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>-9k + 2k - 10 = 0 -&gt; -7k = 10 -&gt; k = -10/7.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Direction cosines of line joining (1, 0, 0) and (0, 1, 1):</text>
            <option id="A">-1/sqrt(3), 1/sqrt(3), 1/sqrt(3)</option><option id="B">1, 1, 0</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>DRs = (-1, 1, 1). Magnitude = sqrt(3).</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Distance of (p, q, r) from Z-axis is:</text>
            <option id="A">sqrt(p^2 + q^2)</option><option id="B">r</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Distance to point (0, 0, r).</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Which point is on line r = (i+2j) + t(k)?</text>
            <option id="A">(1, 2, 5)</option><option id="B">(0, 0, 1)</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>x and y fixed at 1 and 2. z is arbitrary.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Angle between planes r.(2i-j+k) = 6 and r.(i+j+2k) = 5:</text>
            <option id="A">60 degrees</option><option id="B">90 degrees</option><option id="C">45 degrees</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>cos theta = |2-1+2| / (sqrt(6)*sqrt(6)) = 3/6 = 1/2.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Equation of plane through (1,2,3) with DRs of normal 2,3,4:</text>
            <option id="A">2x + 3y + 4z = 20</option><option id="B">2x + 3y + 4z = 0</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>2(1)+3(2)+4(3)=2+6+12=20.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Plane x/2 + y/3 + z/4 = 1 meets axes at A, B, C. Area of triangle ABC:</text>
            <option id="A">sqrt(61)</option><option id="B">sqrt(61)/2? No. Sides check.</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Vertices (2,0,0), (0,3,0), (0,0,4). Vectors AB = (-2,3,0), AC = (-2,0,4). Cross = 12i + 8j + 6k. Magnitude = sqrt(144+64+36) = sqrt(244) = 2 sqrt(61). Area = sqrt(61).</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>If a line makes alpha, beta, gamma with axes, then sin^2 alpha + sin^2 beta + sin^2 gamma = :</text>
            <option id="A">2</option><option id="B">1</option><option id="C">3</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>(1-cos^2 alpha) + ... = 3 - 1 = 2.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Intersection of plane r.n=d and line r=a+tb is unique if:</text>
            <option id="A">b.n != 0</option><option id="B">b.n = 0</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Line must not be parallel to plane.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Distance from origin to plane x+2y-2z+9=0 is:</text>
            <option id="A">3</option><option id="B">9</option><option id="C">sqrt(9)</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>|9| / sqrt(1+4+4) = 9/3 = 3.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Find the foot of perpendicular from (1, 0, 0) to plane x-y+z = 0:</text>
            <option id="A">(2/3, 1/3, -1/3)</option><option id="B">(0, 0, 0)</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Line: (x-1)/1 = (y-0)/-1 = (z-0)/1 = k. Point (k+1, -k, k). Into plane: (k+1) + k + k = 0 -&gt; 3k+1=0 -&gt; k=-1/3.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Condition for points (x1,y1,z1), (x2,y2,z2) to be on same side of plane Ax+By+Cz+D=0:</text>
            <option id="A">(Ax1+By1+Cz1+D)(Ax2+By2+Cz2+D) &gt; 0</option><option id="B">Sum is zero</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Plane expressions have same sign.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>A line is parallel to YZ plane if its DRs satisfy:</text>
